Saru (@sarvanimuppane) started playing Ultimate about 4 years ago. Her enthusiasm and love for the sport are contagious.

She shares with us her journey in this sport, and how the sport has changed her life, along with sharing some of her best memories of playing Ultimate.

She tells us how an injury forced her to stay away from Ultimate, and where she is on the road to getting back. She also shares some stories of her love for adventure in life.

Aishwarya (@aishashoka_01), fondly called Aishu, has been playing Ultimate for 6 years, now. She was introduced to the Sport by her brother Tarle. She quickly went from not having played sports to representing the country at the Worlds in 2016.

In this video, she shares with us how she got into the sport, how the team helped her quickly pick up the sport helping her get the opportunity to play at the highest level. She also shares with us her experiences as a captain of TIKS.

She expresses her gratitude to the Ultimate community and the TIKS family for the support she has received in coping with Tarle's demise in September 2018.

Aprameya(@aprameya33 ), also called Appu, has been playing Ultimate since 5 years. He shares with us, his journey not only in Ultimate, but also in a lot of other sports he's played.

He is an amazing athlete who takes keen interest in long distance running, Kho-Kho, Table Tennis, Badminton, Cricket and many other sports. He also likes to travel and pursue different kinds of adventures when he gets a chance. He's a very jovial person on and off the field. .

He shares his views about mental strength in sports and how to build it. He also speaks about the SOTG and how he feels Ultimate is different from all the other sports he has played. .

Vivek (@holyinsane88), aka VK, is one of the founders of the team and has been playing Ultimate since 2014. He shares with us how the team started off, and what he wants to change in the team now, as a part of the leadership group.

As an athlete who has played a lot of tennis, and has done a lot of long distance running and cycling, he shares with us, how Ultimate is different from them.

He's an adventure enthusiast who likes to have intense experiences, and in this video he shares with us a couple of them, including revealing his secret to being calm on the field.

Shruthi (@travelingshruuum) started playing Ultimate about 3 years ago, with TIKS and is now trying to get back to playing in the Netherlands, where she currently lives. .

She shares with us how she started playing, and how the sport helped her come out of depression alongside professional help that she was getting. She also shares her impressions of the sport through her feminist lenses.

An avid reader and a geek who enjoys engineering and math, she gives us some travel, food and reading recommendations.
.

Naren and Tara joined the TIKS club in the early days, even before we were called TIKS. They play Frisbee for fun, when they are not busy doing some super-fun things like Paragliding or Kayaking.

In this video, Naren shares with us how he got into Flying and Kayaking, and how beginning to teach it deepened his love for the sport. Tara shares her joy of flying and the passion she has for teaching.

We also talk to them about how they met each other, and about their outlook towards life that seems to make them such joyful and happy people.

Pavan (@nayakpavan), or Poan for some of us, has been playing Ultimate for about 4 years. He captained the team during the last season along with @krishnakalro.

He‚Äôs an architect by profession who also enjoys other creative pursuits, especially design and photography. He enjoys playing any sport and you‚Äôd often find him looking for people to play Football or Basketball with, even during a hectic week with lot of Ultimate. He enjoys his share of video-gaming, when outdoor sports is not an option.

He speaks to us, here, about his experiences as a captain of the team, the challenges he faced and the lessons he learnt. He also shares with us what and who inspires him to get better, and a few other glimpses into his Ultimate journey so far, and his hopes and dreams for the future.

Nikitha(@nikitha.nimbalkar), fondly called Nikki, has been playing Ultimate for about 4 years now, and is here sharing with us some highlights from her journey.

She's an amazing dancer and an adventure enthusiast, who actively contributed to her college's mountaineering club. She's a hard worker, both on and off the field. Currently, she spends her (work)days building software to help an online store serve their customers well. Also, she really loves her Biryani, and you better stay away from it. You've been warned!

After an amazing Nationals a couple of months ago, she talks to us about how she got into Ultimate, who inspires her to get better, some thoughts on the last season, what hopes and dreams she has for herself and the team, and how she looks at her role in the team's leadership group.

We are delighted to announced that One All founder, Varsha Yeshwant Kumar has got the Acumen fellowship for 2020!
The Acumen Fellows Program is a one-year leadership development program designed to connect and cultivate a pipeline of social changemakers who are committed to tackling poverty and injustice in their communities.
Varsha is one of 23 people from India who have received this fellowship. One All hopes that she will have a great learning experience which will cause a ripple effect in our community!
